The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as image synthesis and object detection, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of 3D models and alignment techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The proposed technique involves extracting structural information and making use of correlations, which are common themes in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the possibility of using the synthesized images for object detection, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO).
